[src:solidjs/frameworks-libraries] JavaScript frameworks are an essential part of modern front-end web development, providing developers with tried and tested tools for building scalable, interactive web applications.
[src:solidjs/frameworks-libraries] Many modern companies use frameworks as a standard part of their tooling, so many front-end development jobs now require framework experience.
[src:solidjs/frameworks-libraries] This set of articles provides a comfortable starting point to help you begin learning frameworks.
[src:solidjs/frameworks-libraries] We are not aiming to exhaustively teach you everything you need to know about React/ReactDOM, or Vue, or some other specific framework; the framework teams' own docs (and other resources) do that job already.
[src:solidjs/frameworks-libraries] After that, we'll provide some tutorials covering the essentials React, a popular framework choice, to provide you with enough context and familiarity to start going into greater depth yourself.
[src:solidjs/frameworks-libraries] We want you to go forward and learn about frameworks in a pragmatic way that doesn't forget about web platform fundamental best practices such as accessibility.
[src:solidjs/frameworks-libraries] We also provide some tutorials covering the basics of other framework choices, for those who want to make a different choice to React.
[src:solidjs/frameworks-libraries] You should really learn the basics of the core web languages first before attempting to move on to learning client-side frameworks — HTML, CSS, and especially JavaScript.
[src:solidjs/frameworks-libraries] Your code will be richer and more professional as a result, and you'll be able to troubleshoot problems with more confidence if you understand the fundamental web platform features that the frameworks are building on top of.
[src:solidjs/frameworks-libraries] We begin our look at frameworks with a general overview of the area, looking at a brief history of JavaScript and frameworks, why frameworks exist and what they give us, how to start thinking about choosing a framework to learn, and what alternatives there are to client-side frameworks.
[src:solidjs/frameworks-libraries] Each major JavaScript framework has a different approach to updating the DOM, handling browser events, and providing an enjoyable developer experience.
[src:solidjs/frameworks-libraries] This article will explore the main features of "the big 4" frameworks, looking at how frameworks tend to work from a high level and the differences between them.
